node.title: One new COVID case detected in Queensland as state tracks a week ahead for vaccination target
node.alt: Dr Peter Aitken speaks at a media conference in Brisbane.
node.description: Queensland records one new case of coronavirus as the state tracks towards hitting the 80 per cent double vaccination milestone on December 10.
node.content:
["Queensland has recorded one new case of coronavirus as the state tracks towards hitting the\u00a080 per cent double vaccination milestone on December 10, Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken\u00a0says.", "The infection was detected in hotel quarantine, with the person a family member of three unvaccinated Melburnians who tested positive earlier this week.", "Dr Aitkin said when looking at the latest vaccination rates, the state was on track to loosen border restrictions a week ahead of schedule.", "Of those aged 16 and over, 85.81\u00a0per cent have had a single dose of the vaccine\u00a0and 75.3 per cent were double dosed.", "\"The timelines for 80 per cent\u00a0double vaccinated as far as border movements\u00a0and quarantine, still looking at the 10th, but it does change day by day, depending on the vaccination numbers,\" he said.", "At 80 per cent, travellers from hotspots will be able to travel into Queensland without quarantining, however they will have to be fully vaccinated and pass a COVID test 72 hours ahead of arrival.", "
New strain a concern for health officials
", "Dr Aitken said the peak body comprised of state and territory chief health officers, the Australian Health Protection Principal Committee, would meet later today to discuss the new COVID variant, Omicron, that is emerging in South Africa, where just a quarter of the population is vaccinated.", "The federal government is expected to announce changes to quarantine rules for people who have been in South Africa recently.", "Dr Aitken said there was no evidence that the variant was in Queensland, or Australia.", "He did not believe the new variant would change the deadlines for international borders reopening in Queensland, due in early January.", "\u201cAt the moment from a Queensland perspective we keep doing what we\u2019re doing,\" he said.", "Mater Queensland's infectious diseases unit head, Paul Griffin, said vaccinations would still provide a layer of protection against the Omicron variant.", "\"Well, it's pretty easy to actually change them these days,\" he said.", "\"We can put that new sequence into the vaccine platforms that we have and make new vaccines to combat this variant as well.", "\"It's not really the doomsday scenario that someone's describing it as but it does seem to be a fairly significant event at the moment.\""]
